                            <comment id="49753" author="bogl" created="Fri, 28 Dec 2012 12:52:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When I put up a pure b2_3 sles11 sp2 client I still wasn&apos;t able to reproduce the problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The msg output reported suggests the client is seeing -12 (-ENOMEM), which is the expected error generated by the fail_loc value set in the test.  strace output of the touch command suggests that error is being reported up to the touch command.  I&apos;m not sure how the test could fail that being the case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="49752" author="bogl" created="Fri, 28 Dec 2012 11:52:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Haven&apos;t been able to reproduce this problem with current (2.3.57) Centos servers and sles11 sp2 client.  Suggests this problem is probably version specific.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="49736" author="pjones" created="Thu, 27 Dec 2012 21:19:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bob&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please look into this one?&lt;/p&gt;

